The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | First day first show
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      First day first show
          
	Calcuttans came out in droves to celebrate New Year, bundled in layers of woollens but enjoying the nip in the air. A Metro round-up of the festive zones              Like every year, a rich Raj legacy and luxurious lawns made Victoria Memorial a top draw on January 1   Others walked the pilgrim rsquo;s path and thronged Dakshineswar   to offer puja on Kalpataru festival on Friday              The sunny winter morning added to the merry mood   at the Alipore zoo on Friday  For many Calcuttans, all decked up and bets in hand, a day at the races   was the best way to start the year              Families, especially those with little children, trooped to   Millennium Park for a lazy day by the riverside  The musically inclined crowned the first evening of 2010 at a recital by   Ustad Amjad Ali Khan at Science City      
	Pictures by Sanjoy Chattopadhyaya, Sanat Kumar Sinha, Anindya Shankar Ray, 
